        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 1:58AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 157 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Knowles, or 12 miles northeast of Beaver, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Knowles.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
